    <item>
      <title>Action segmentation using public dataset</title>
      <link>/project/action/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2019 00:00:00 +0900</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/project/action/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h2 id=&#34;contents&#34;&gt;Contents&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Human action segmentation task using public fine-grained video datasets(50salads, breakfast, gtea). We used TCN(Temporal Neaural Networks)for the segmentation part. For the extracting part, we used 3DCNN models (I3D).
You can see the full code &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/t-koba-96/TCNModels&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Follow the readme.md to train and test on these local datasets.&lt;br /&gt;
Also, if you want more info for the demo, check out my &lt;a href=&#34;/blog/demo&#34;&gt;blog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

